WEBVTT

00:06.615 --> 00:09.052
Dre: <i>Love is a lot</i> <i>
like the club.</i>

00:09.096 --> 00:11.359
<i>In order to get in,</i> <i>
you've got to be</i>

00:11.402 --> 00:13.752
<i>with the right person</i> <i>
at the right time.</i>

00:13.796 --> 00:16.451
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah

00:16.494 --> 00:18.192
<i>It doesn't always work out.</i>

00:18.235 --> 00:21.064
[ Buzzer ]♪ Baby, if you want me

00:21.108 --> 00:23.806
♪ You've got to show me love

00:23.849 --> 00:26.156
<i>And just because you're</i> <i>
in the club,</i>

00:26.200 --> 00:28.985
<i>doesn't mean you're</i> <i>
popping bottles in VIP.</i>

00:29.029 --> 00:33.772
♪ You've got to show me love

00:33.816 --> 00:37.385
<i>Only the lucky ones</i> <i>
find true love that lasts.</i>

00:37.428 --> 00:40.301
<i>It's a beautiful thing,</i> <i>
Club Love.</i>

00:40.344 --> 00:42.129
<i>I just wish everyone</i> <i>
could get in.</i>

00:44.218 --> 00:46.046
Fellas, I got some big news.

00:46.089 --> 00:47.612
Hmm?
Yeah?

00:47.656 --> 00:50.746
I'm getting married
this weekend!

00:50.789 --> 00:51.964
Wow.

00:52.008 --> 00:53.705
<i>Aw, hell.</i>

00:53.749 --> 00:56.447
<i>Now they're letting anyone</i> <i>
into VIP.</i>

01:01.452 --> 01:03.150
Y-You're getting married?

01:03.193 --> 01:04.890
I didn't even know
you were dating someone,

01:04.934 --> 01:06.892
or not already married.

01:06.936 --> 01:09.286
Dre, now you know
how famously private I am.

01:09.330 --> 01:11.158
I'm very careful
when it comes to my heart

01:11.201 --> 01:12.463
and my debt collectors.

01:12.507 --> 01:14.465
But today,
I'm so happy,

01:14.509 --> 01:16.989
I want to shout my love
from the rooftops.

01:17.033 --> 01:21.907
I am marrying
Vivica A. Fox!

01:21.951 --> 01:23.126
What?
What?

01:23.170 --> 01:24.997
Wait, "Soul Food"
Vivica A. Fox?

01:25.041 --> 01:27.609
Uh, "Kill Bill"
Vivica A. Fox?

01:27.652 --> 01:29.219
"Booty Call"
Vivica A. Fox?

01:29.263 --> 01:31.961
"Two Can Play That Game"
Vivica A. Fox?

01:32.004 --> 01:34.616
Yes, darlings,
all of those women.

01:34.659 --> 01:35.878
All: Whoa.

01:35.921 --> 01:38.141
- There's my Paisley Prince.
- Yes.

01:38.185 --> 01:39.838
I just had to come in here
and see your handsome face.

01:39.882 --> 01:42.276
Oh. Mwah.

01:42.319 --> 01:46.149
Gentlemen, meet the future
Mrs. Charlie Telphy A. Fox.

01:46.193 --> 01:47.237
Hey.

01:47.281 --> 01:48.760
- Hey.
- Hey!

01:48.804 --> 01:50.110
The moon to my stars.

01:50.153 --> 01:52.634
Ooh. He's the straw
that stirs my drink.

01:52.677 --> 01:54.026
The quarter
to my parking meter.

01:54.070 --> 01:55.941
The lemon pepper
on my wings.

01:55.985 --> 01:57.595
The toothpick that keeps
my sandwich together.

01:57.639 --> 01:59.771
Okay, I feel like
- this could go on forever.
- Yep.

01:59.815 --> 02:01.860
Uh, excuse me, I don't --
Uh, just one quick question.

02:01.904 --> 02:02.948
Don't take
this the wrong way... Mm-hmm.

02:02.992 --> 02:05.560
...but why on
God's green earth

02:05.603 --> 02:08.258
are you marrying him?
Why?

02:08.302 --> 02:10.956
When you've spent your life
around A-list actors,

02:11.000 --> 02:13.611
A-list athletes,
A-list rappers,

02:13.655 --> 02:15.874
you want someone
who's real,

02:15.918 --> 02:18.138
someone who reminds you
of what's important.

02:18.181 --> 02:19.965
Charlie opened up
my heart.

02:20.009 --> 02:21.358
- Charlie: That's right.
- Aww.

02:21.402 --> 02:22.968
And when you find that person,
you don't want to wait

02:23.012 --> 02:24.318
another minute
to get married.

02:24.361 --> 02:25.928
That's why we're getting
married on Saturday.

02:25.971 --> 02:27.103
- Satur--
- What?

02:27.147 --> 02:28.583
Check your spam folders
for E-vites.

02:28.626 --> 02:30.541
And if you're wondering,
we're registered at Mercedes.

02:31.934 --> 02:33.631
<i>So, that night, we broke bread</i>

02:33.675 --> 02:35.590
<i>with Charlie</i> <i>
and his new fiancée.</i>

02:35.633 --> 02:39.202
<i>It was the least we could do,</i> <i>
and it was Bow's idea.</i>

02:40.986 --> 02:42.597
I'm really glad
we can do this

02:42.640 --> 02:44.338
without it being
awkward between us.

02:44.381 --> 02:45.861
Mm.

02:45.904 --> 02:47.558
Who's "us"? What?

02:47.602 --> 02:48.951
It's okay, Bow.

02:48.994 --> 02:50.344
I know Charlie
had feelings for you,

02:50.387 --> 02:51.823
and I'm cool with it.

02:51.867 --> 02:55.262
Why wouldn't he be attracted
to a smart, talented woman?

02:55.305 --> 02:57.264
Because that woman
is my wife?

02:57.307 --> 02:58.265
Sweetie.
Hmm?

02:58.308 --> 02:59.788
My ring
doesn't cover my face.

03:02.443 --> 03:04.662
Sharp and sexy.

03:04.706 --> 03:06.664
You know, you really hit the
Powerball with this one, Dre.

03:06.708 --> 03:08.797
Oh, look at that. I love her.
I love this woman.

03:08.840 --> 03:10.799
Vivica Fox!
Cheers!

03:10.842 --> 03:12.975
Hey. Hey.

03:13.018 --> 03:14.759
Hey, hey, Charlie,
let's go grab a drink.

03:14.803 --> 03:16.848
- Okay.
- Uh, Diane, could you take care of the dishes?

03:16.892 --> 03:18.763
And, uh, Jack... Yeah.

03:18.807 --> 03:21.375
...can you put on that
"grown folks" playlist
that you curated?

03:21.418 --> 03:23.203
- Gotcha.
- Charlie: Be right back, baby.

03:23.246 --> 03:25.683
Mm-hmm.
Let me help you.

03:25.727 --> 03:26.815
Okay.

03:26.858 --> 03:28.599
Thanks, Diane. Yep.

03:28.643 --> 03:31.036
Alright, I like
to leave the utensils

03:31.080 --> 03:33.169
facing points up,
just for fun.

03:33.213 --> 03:35.911
Yeah, whatever.
Look here, little girl.

03:35.954 --> 03:38.218
Huh?
We need to have a talk.

03:38.261 --> 03:40.307
That man in there means
the world to me,

03:40.350 --> 03:42.265
and even the sound
of your name

03:42.309 --> 03:43.832
makes the light
go out in his eyes.

03:43.875 --> 03:45.921
Yeah.

03:47.488 --> 03:49.533
That's why I don't want you
anywhere near my wedding.

03:49.577 --> 03:51.056
Vivica?
Ah, ah.

03:51.100 --> 03:53.189
I said what I said.

03:53.233 --> 03:54.843
Don't you try to play me, Diane.

03:56.888 --> 04:00.370
Let me get one more
slice of that delicious cake.

04:02.067 --> 04:06.594
How many "Set It Off" cast
members am I gonna feud with?

04:06.637 --> 04:10.554
Charlie, man, I've never seen
you this happy before,

04:10.598 --> 04:12.513
but there is a sparkle
in your eye,

04:12.556 --> 04:16.256
a pep in your step,
and not a stain on your shirt.

04:16.299 --> 04:18.301
Thank you so much
for doing this for us, Dre.

04:18.345 --> 04:20.347
- Mm-hmm.
- I mean, I really, really

04:20.390 --> 04:23.132
appreciate it,
so much so, man,

04:23.175 --> 04:26.831
that I...I want to ask you
to be my best man.

04:28.485 --> 04:29.486
I'd be honored.

04:29.530 --> 04:31.227
Thanks, Dre.

04:31.271 --> 04:32.707
- Mm-hmm.
- I appreciate it, man.

04:32.750 --> 04:34.535
Mmm.

04:34.578 --> 04:36.493
Mmm.
This is smooth.

04:36.537 --> 04:38.147
Yep.

04:38.190 --> 04:40.367
Make sure you bring a handle
of this to the bachelor party.

04:40.410 --> 04:42.020
Mm.
Bachelor party?

04:42.064 --> 04:43.631
Well, if you gonna throw one,
I ain't gonna stop you.

04:43.674 --> 04:44.980
Hey.

04:45.023 --> 04:47.199
I have Thursday conveniently
open while Vivica

04:47.243 --> 04:50.115
go gets her premarital wax,
so get to planning.

04:50.159 --> 04:52.553
Okay.
Y-You know what, Charlie?

04:52.596 --> 04:53.684
I'll put something
together for you.

04:53.728 --> 04:55.164
My man.
Thank you so much.
Mm-hmm.

04:55.207 --> 04:56.339
And it ain't got
to be nothing special,

04:56.383 --> 04:57.775
nothing big,
nothing like that.

04:57.819 --> 04:59.386
Maybe you want to look into
getting us on

04:59.429 --> 05:03.041
one of those civilian
spaceship trips, that'd be cool.

05:03.085 --> 05:04.565
No.
I mean, yeah,
just surprise me.

05:04.608 --> 05:06.218
It's all good.

05:06.262 --> 05:09.091
<i>If you asked a lesser man</i> <i>
to plan a bachelor party</i>

05:09.134 --> 05:11.528
<i>in two days, you'd end up</i> <i>
riding go-karts</i>

05:11.572 --> 05:13.922
<i>before your reservation</i> <i>
at Applebee's.</i>

05:13.965 --> 05:16.141
<i>But that's not how I roll.</i>

05:19.449 --> 05:20.668
What?!

05:20.711 --> 05:22.365
Oh, wow!

05:22.409 --> 05:24.889
- Come on, Dre!
- Mm-hmm.

05:24.933 --> 05:26.630
Oh!
Reba McEntire's playing.

05:26.674 --> 05:28.284
Can we go? Please?

05:28.328 --> 05:30.330
You have really outdone
yourself, Dre.

05:30.373 --> 05:31.722
Well...

05:31.766 --> 05:34.334
Well, all I did
was secure a suite,

05:34.377 --> 05:37.511
a rare tequila tasting,
our own private blackjack table,

05:37.554 --> 05:40.035
and front row seats
to see David Blaine

05:40.078 --> 05:41.819
stick a skewer
through his cheek.

05:41.863 --> 05:43.343
- Nice.
- Anybody could've did that.

05:43.386 --> 05:45.475
Can you believe him?

05:45.519 --> 05:47.608
He literally opened
up his laptop for five minutes

05:47.651 --> 05:48.609
and booked a concierge.

05:48.652 --> 05:49.784
<i>That's so your dad.</i>

05:49.827 --> 05:50.959
Tell her
I'm also ripping up

05:51.002 --> 05:52.874
your Cirque du Soleil
tickets, son.

05:52.917 --> 05:55.224
Not the circus...

05:55.267 --> 05:56.791
We're going
to Cirque du Soleil?

05:56.834 --> 05:58.401
Hey, guys, bathroom break,
and then we're gonna saddle up

05:58.445 --> 05:59.837
and take a ride
around the casino.

05:59.881 --> 06:01.099
- Oh-ho-ho!
- Got it.

06:01.143 --> 06:02.927
Bathroom break?
Wink, wink.

06:02.971 --> 06:04.364
I'll be right back.

06:04.407 --> 06:06.235
This is all too incredible, Dre.

06:06.278 --> 06:09.412
Hey, I'm the best man.
I don't half-step.

06:09.456 --> 06:11.066
You know how
to make a man

06:11.109 --> 06:12.110
feel special,
don't you?

06:14.417 --> 06:16.985
And that same special feeling,
I want Vivica to feel

06:17.028 --> 06:19.509
when I put that ring
- on her finger, you know?
- Mm-hmm.

06:19.553 --> 06:21.032
So,
if it's cool with you,

06:21.076 --> 06:22.773
I need to hold down 10 Gs,
my man.

06:22.817 --> 06:24.209
What?

06:24.253 --> 06:26.473
Oh, I'm sorry.
My <i>best</i> man.

06:26.516 --> 06:28.170
Hell no.

06:28.213 --> 06:31.086
What? Look, I got
a Hollywood girl right now.

06:31.129 --> 06:33.305
I can't be buying her
no North Hollywood ring.

06:33.349 --> 06:35.438
Charlie, are you out
of your damn mind?

06:35.482 --> 06:38.354
What makes you think that I
would let you hold 10 grand?

06:38.398 --> 06:39.921
Why wouldn't you?
You're my best friend.

06:39.964 --> 06:42.271
Who else would I ask?

06:42.314 --> 06:43.968
You think
I'm your best friend?

06:44.012 --> 06:46.231
Yeah.
Charlie, how can we
be best friends?

06:46.275 --> 06:47.929
I don't know your birthday. I
don't know your favorite color.

06:47.972 --> 06:49.800
I-I've never been
to your crib.

06:49.844 --> 06:51.411
- Have you ever asked?
- Come on, Charlie.

06:51.454 --> 06:53.978
You're great,
but we work together, man.

06:54.022 --> 06:56.416
We're not frat brothers.
We don't vacation together.

06:56.459 --> 06:59.593
I mean, I'm not even sure
you get my Christmas cards.

06:59.636 --> 07:02.944
Um...

07:02.987 --> 07:05.033
I guess I made a miscalculation.

07:05.076 --> 07:07.339
Okay, don't ask me why,

07:07.383 --> 07:10.168
but, uh,
I got a lot more energy

07:10.212 --> 07:12.257
than I did before,
and, uh, I'm gonna feel

07:12.301 --> 07:13.824
a lot sadder
in about two hours,

07:13.868 --> 07:15.913
so let's party
before this wears off.

07:15.957 --> 07:16.827
Come on!
Whoo!

07:16.871 --> 07:18.568
- Come on!
- Party!

07:18.612 --> 07:21.223
Prostitutes!
Whoo!

07:21.266 --> 07:22.267
Hmm.

07:25.706 --> 07:27.751
Dre: Babe.
Hey.

07:27.795 --> 07:31.059
So, I didn't get any phone calls
from the credit card company

07:31.102 --> 07:33.017
about suspicious activity
on our card.

07:33.061 --> 07:35.019
Did you not
have fun last night?

07:35.063 --> 07:36.586
I did not. Oh.

07:36.630 --> 07:38.675
But there's a reason
I don't hang out

07:38.719 --> 07:40.547
with those people
after the bank closes.

07:40.590 --> 07:43.680
Oh-ho-ho-ho.
Here comes another Dre story.

07:43.724 --> 07:45.116
What's Johan doing here?

07:45.160 --> 07:46.901
What? I can't come visit
my favorite sister

07:46.944 --> 07:48.119
without you giving me
a hard time?

07:48.163 --> 07:49.512
Mm.

07:49.556 --> 07:52.036
Fine.
Had to leave India.

07:52.080 --> 07:53.864
Told the wrong person
to Namaste.

07:53.908 --> 07:55.997
Ah.
That's more like it.

07:56.040 --> 07:59.479
So, how was it, Dre?
What happened?

07:59.522 --> 08:02.351
I mean, you guys must've been
like red meat for the con-women.

08:02.394 --> 08:04.048
You know what?

08:04.092 --> 08:06.398
Charlie lost his damn mind.

08:06.442 --> 08:09.750
Oh.
He thinks
he is my best friend.

08:13.623 --> 08:15.407
- Your best friend?
- Mm-hmm.

08:15.451 --> 08:16.974
Dre, that's crazy.
You don't have any friends.

08:17.018 --> 08:18.454
Yeah.
Yes, I do.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.456
- Who?
- I've never seen you converse with one friend.

08:20.500 --> 08:21.849
Unh-unh.

08:21.892 --> 08:24.112
Dre, come on, you lost
your phone for three days,

08:24.155 --> 08:26.506
and the only missed call
was from Domino's.

08:26.549 --> 08:29.160
That's because my friend,
Willie, works there.

08:29.204 --> 08:30.901
Face it, Dre,
since we've been married,

08:30.945 --> 08:32.250
you only hang out
with me.

08:32.294 --> 08:35.166
What? If anything,
I have too many friends.

08:35.210 --> 08:37.560
- Hmm.
- Charlie thinks he's my number one.

08:37.604 --> 08:38.996
He's not even
in my top 10.

08:39.040 --> 08:40.084
Huh.

08:40.128 --> 08:41.999
So, you think
you have enough friends

08:42.043 --> 08:44.611
for a five-on-five
basketball game?

08:44.654 --> 08:46.134
- I do.
- Name them.

08:46.177 --> 08:48.005
I will. Okay.

08:48.049 --> 08:49.224
T-Will.
Mm-hmm.

08:49.267 --> 08:50.138
Ronnie.

08:50.181 --> 08:51.966
Ladarius, Tony.

08:52.009 --> 08:54.359
Gigi, Sha,
Cousin Gary.

08:54.403 --> 08:55.622
No.
Pizza Willie.

08:55.665 --> 08:57.362
That's...

08:57.406 --> 08:58.842
Me.

08:58.886 --> 09:00.583
Dre, you haven't seen any
of those people in years,

09:00.627 --> 09:01.932
and one of them is dead.

09:01.976 --> 09:03.586
RIP Tony.

09:03.630 --> 09:06.197
Mm-hmm. And you hang out
with Charlie all the time.

09:06.241 --> 09:08.591
Because of work.
Alright?

09:08.635 --> 09:11.289
Babe, I'm like doughnuts
in that office.

09:11.333 --> 09:13.074
Okay.
Everybody loves me.

09:13.117 --> 09:14.597
- Mm-hmm.
- Charlie ain't special.

09:14.641 --> 09:16.425
Okay.

09:16.468 --> 09:19.210
Great. Now that we've solved
that, I'll be in your bathroom.

09:19.254 --> 09:22.300
- Hmm.
- I need to make sure no parasites followed me back from Bengal.

09:22.344 --> 09:24.389
Yeah.

09:24.433 --> 09:25.565
Ew.

09:28.959 --> 09:31.005
All this stuff happened yesterday.

09:31.048 --> 09:33.224
I mean,
why do people read this?

09:33.268 --> 09:34.661
Hey.

09:34.704 --> 09:36.271
Since we're not going
to Charles' wedding,

09:36.314 --> 09:38.099
should we all get tickets
to Splash Down Falls?

09:38.142 --> 09:39.535
Hmm?

09:39.579 --> 09:40.841
Look, they're double-bleaching
the lazy river now,

09:40.884 --> 09:42.190
so no one should get
an infection.

09:42.233 --> 09:43.278
Oh, I'm going
to that wedding.

09:43.321 --> 09:44.496
Oh, yeah, me, too.

09:44.540 --> 09:47.021
I love love
and free food.
Mm-hmm.

09:47.064 --> 09:48.979
So, you guys are just gonna
leave Jack and I behind

09:49.023 --> 09:50.502
like we're not a part
of this family?

09:50.546 --> 09:52.026
I mean... Oh.

09:52.069 --> 09:53.549
Mm...

09:53.593 --> 09:55.203
Are you kidding me?

09:55.246 --> 09:57.771
Jack, I would never go to a
party if you weren't invited.

09:57.814 --> 09:59.947
You only go to parties
if I'm <i>not</i> invited.

09:59.990 --> 10:01.949
Well, you're unpopular.
That's not my fault.

10:01.992 --> 10:04.299
Okay, I'm sorry, but you're on
the haters list, not me.

10:04.342 --> 10:05.996
Wow.

10:06.040 --> 10:07.824
Why do you want to go so bad,
anyway?

10:07.868 --> 10:09.391
Yeah.
I don't.
I couldn't care less.

10:09.434 --> 10:10.827
Oh, sounds like
you care.

10:10.871 --> 10:12.307
You don't know me, hippie.

10:12.350 --> 10:15.440
Okay, look, Diane, if you want
to go to the wedding,

10:15.484 --> 10:16.964
you just gotta make things right
with Charlie.

10:17.007 --> 10:18.922
Yeah. Vivica just wants him
to be happy.

10:18.966 --> 10:21.621
I mean, maybe if you
and Charlie are cool,

10:21.664 --> 10:22.926
she'll be okay
with you going.

10:22.970 --> 10:25.059
Pass.
Enjoy your stupid wedding.

10:25.102 --> 10:26.713
I hope it's a buffet
and your table goes last.

10:26.756 --> 10:28.149
Mm-hmm.

10:28.192 --> 10:31.761
Wow. What happened with her
and Charlie, anyway?

10:31.805 --> 10:35.112
Well, it's complicated,
but it all started when...

10:36.461 --> 10:39.334
Oh! Hey, babe.

10:39.377 --> 10:40.683
Sorry, gotta take this.

10:40.727 --> 10:43.381
Oh, yo,
I am in front of family.

10:47.342 --> 10:49.910
Dre: <i>Bow made her argument,</i>

10:49.953 --> 10:52.173
<i>but it wasn't my fault</i> <i>
that Charlie didn't understand</i>

10:52.216 --> 10:54.262
<i>what our friendship was</i> <i>
and wasn't.</i>

10:54.305 --> 10:56.090
<i>And truth?</i>

10:56.133 --> 10:58.832
<i>Everybody at the office thought</i> <i>
I was their best friend.</i>

10:58.875 --> 11:00.572
James.

11:00.616 --> 11:03.837
Can you explain to me this
whole, uh, overnight oats thing?

11:03.880 --> 11:06.448
Uh, well, you just pour the milk
on top of the oats

11:06.491 --> 11:08.885
and let them sit in
the refrigerator overnight.

11:08.929 --> 11:10.365
Oh, oh,
what about the fruit?

11:10.408 --> 11:13.020
Do you put that on before,
or do you put it on after?

11:13.063 --> 11:15.500
I don't know, man.
I didn't go to oatmeal college.

11:17.764 --> 11:19.417
Oatmeal college.

11:21.071 --> 11:23.073
Oh, wow, Maddie.
