you're Charlie's best man?

14:44.666 --> 14:46.450
Listen, I'm sorry, Dad,
but you blew it, alright?

14:46.494 --> 14:48.017
He turned to me.

14:48.061 --> 14:50.324
Well, actually, he turned
to his Starbucks barista,

14:50.367 --> 14:53.109
Brendan, but he had
a prior conflict.

14:53.153 --> 14:55.155
Although, he did send
the entire wedding party

14:55.198 --> 14:56.504
their favorite drinks.

14:56.547 --> 14:58.549
He's a great guy.
They go way back.

14:58.593 --> 15:01.552
Anyway, I've already got the
rings in my pocket, and, uh,

15:01.596 --> 15:04.338
in case you're wondering, you
missed out on a very nice flask.

15:04.381 --> 15:06.470
- Let me just talk to him.
- No, no, no, no.

15:06.514 --> 15:08.385
I don't think so.
Alright?

15:08.429 --> 15:09.691
Step away from the door.

15:09.734 --> 15:11.911
You really hurt Charlie.

15:11.954 --> 15:14.000
He was broken.

15:14.043 --> 15:16.524
Luckily, Brendan and I were
there to pick up the pieces.

15:16.567 --> 15:18.047
Look,
I know I messed up,

15:18.091 --> 15:19.483
but, Charlie,
if you give me one more ch--

15:19.527 --> 15:21.007
Mnh-mnh!

15:21.050 --> 15:23.661
Today of all days,
Charlie deserves to be up there

15:23.705 --> 15:26.142
with someone he trusts.

15:26.186 --> 15:27.404
But he trusts me.

15:27.448 --> 15:28.710
Mnh-mnh.

15:28.753 --> 15:32.409
Dad, don't embarrass
yourself, alright?

15:32.453 --> 15:34.020
Now, I gotta go.

15:34.063 --> 15:35.935
I gotta find "White Hennessy,"
which at first

15:35.978 --> 15:38.198
I thought was a liquor,
but turns out to be a guest.

15:39.939 --> 15:44.334
<i>I had missed my chance to make</i> <i>
things right with Charlie.</i>

15:44.378 --> 15:48.295
<i>I messed everything up, and he</i> <i>
was moving on without me.</i>

15:50.123 --> 15:52.212
I don't need
this funky wedding.

15:55.215 --> 15:56.042
Diane?

15:58.305 --> 16:00.307
What are you doing
working this wedding?

16:00.350 --> 16:03.353
