The guy's a dud.

16:19.108 --> 16:20.980
No, no, no.

16:21.023 --> 16:23.591
Diane, he's not, though.

16:23.634 --> 16:25.419
He's funny.
He's loyal.

16:25.462 --> 16:28.248
He -- He listens
to all my problems,

16:28.291 --> 16:30.728
and he knows me better than
anybody outside of my family.

16:32.556 --> 16:37.039
And I never took the time
to appreciate what we had.

16:37.083 --> 16:40.695
Normally...
I would say forget him.

16:40.738 --> 16:42.653
He's a drain of resources
on this county,

16:42.697 --> 16:44.003
state, and humanity.

16:46.309 --> 16:48.181
But it seems like
Charlie means a lot to you.

16:50.313 --> 16:53.229
While I disagree
with that decision,

16:53.273 --> 16:55.188
it's not every day
your friend gets married.

16:57.407 --> 16:58.408
You're right, Diane.

16:59.801 --> 17:02.108
Maybe the best thing
that I can do for Charlie

17:02.151 --> 17:05.633
is to just sit back and watch
my best friend get married.

17:07.852 --> 17:11.117
That was some pretty mature
advice you just gave me.

17:11.160 --> 17:13.597
Thank you. Alright.

17:13.641 --> 17:15.817
Well, I better get back in there
and do place settings

17:15.860 --> 17:17.210
or Jerry's
gonna have my ass.

17:17.253 --> 17:18.994
Mm-hmm.

17:19.038 --> 17:21.866
<i>Even if Charlie</i> <i>
didn't want me up there,</i>

17:21.910 --> 17:24.652
<i>I could still celebrate</i> <i>
with him on his day.</i>

